{"notes": "The direct curve_slope read (2s10s at 1.06, flat vs. prior) is itself the best-informed slope input: it's fresh, and it explicitly reconciles the recent bounce off lows against a stalled medium-term flattening trend (63d -0.12pp, 252d -0.38pp, range position 13th percentile). I anchor on this: no durable steepening yet, longer-run bias still flattening, but near-term likely range-bound.

